# ----- Python -----
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.egg-info/
.venv/
venv/
env/

# ----- IDE / OS -----
.vscode/
.idea/
# Cursor agent rules ARE tracked so they apply across machines / cloud
# agents.  Everything else in .cursor/ (plans, indexes, etc.) stays local.
# Pattern note: we cannot ignore .cursor/ wholesale and then re-include a
# child -- git's negation rules require the parent directory not to be
# excluded.  So we ignore the specific children we don't want instead.
.cursor/plans/
.cursor/indexes/
.cursor/agent-transcripts/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ----- Scratch / one-off helpers -----
# Disposable utilities like _peek_hh.py, _reconstruct_lineups.py, _show_top.py.
# Top-level files starting with an underscore are treated as scratch and
# excluded from version control.
/_*.py

# ----- Data + caches -----
# Cached Statcast pulls are organized into data/<year>/ subfolders.
# Prior-season folders are immutable and committed to the repo so codespaces
# start warm. The current-season folder rolls forward daily and is ignored.
# Update this line at the start of each new MLB season.
data/2026/

# pybaseball http cache
.pybaseball/

# ----- Generated reports -----
# All matchup/lineup reports go to reports/<YYYY-MM-DD>/ and are regenerable.
reports/

# Sandbox output for smoke tests.  matchup.py --out-dir sandbox/ writes
# here so smoke runs cannot clobber archived reports/<date>/ artifacts
# (slate.json especially -- not in git, only lives in the working tree).
sandbox/

# ----- Per-run logs -----
# Each script run tees stdout/stderr to logs/<timestamp>/<script>.log via
# log_setup.py. Keep them out of version control.
logs/

# Per-player summary scratch outputs (regenerable)
*_summary.md
*_pitcher_summary.md

# Daily lineup pulls from fetch_lineups.py.
# Current convention: matchups/matchups_<date>_<HHMMSS>.csv (date + time
# stamped, multiple per day as lineups firm up).
# Legacy: matchups_<date>.csv at repo root + .bak.* pre-overwrite snapshots
# from before the merge-aware rewrite.
matchups/
matchups_*.csv
matchups_*.csv.*.bak

# BPP park factor data is tracked so the Cursor Cloud Agent's daily.py
# run (and any other CI / shared machine) has the same park factors the
# local run sees -- otherwise reports come out with neutral park=1.000
# and the published site loses a real signal.  Contains:
#   - annual_park_factors_2023_2025.json (our transcription of BPP's
#     annual archive; the de-parking baseline)
#   - ParkFactors_<date>*.csv (daily game-level BPP CSV)
#   - PlayerParkFactors_<date>*.xlsx (daily per-batter BPP XLSX)
# Repo owner has the BPP subscription that produces the daily files.

# Misc
*.log
kyle_bradish_vs_yankees_hitters.txt
